	<string name="moon_apogee_message">At apogee, the Moon\'s attraction is too weak: seedlings sprout poorly, remain weak, and become vulnerable to disease.
	\nIt is therefore not recommended to garden 5 hours before and after the Moon\'s apogee.</string>
	<string name="moon_perigee_message">When the Moon is at perigee, its attraction is too strong: seedlings become leggy, wither, and produce more fragile plants.
	\nSo avoid working in the garden 5 hours before and after the Moon\'s perigee.</string>
	<string name="moon_node_message">When the Moon crosses the Earth\'s orbital plane, this corresponds to a lunar node.
	This event occurs twice during a lunar month: once at the ascending node and once at the descending node.
	\nBecause the Moon\'s influence is not favorable at these times, it is not recommended to garden 5 hours before and after these nodes.</string>

